title: CHINO: Three big rigs crash, blocking lanes of westbound 60 freeway (UPDATE 2)
text:
Published: Oct. 5, 2015 Updated: 6:40 a.m. CHINO: Three big rigs crash, blocking lanes of westbound 60 freeway (UPDATE 2) Print Photo Share Pin It More Galleries ADVERTISEMENT Related article Â» Updates with lanes opened
A FedEx tractor-trailer crashed into the center divider on the westbound 60 freeway in Chino early Monday morning, Oct. 5, triggering a SigAlert that lasted for hours and created a 10-mile traffic backup.
The lanes were closed at Reservoir Street, about a mile east of the 71 freeway, from 1:45 a.m. to about 6:30 a.m.
The eastbound car pool lane remained closed at 6:30 a.m., the California Highway Patrol said, and there was no estimated time for it to reopen.
The crash was reported as heavy rain was falling in the area, according to the CHP.
This story is developing. Watch PE.com for updates.
